    "For instance, empirical evidence from studies on video game design suggests that players might develop empathy towards their in-game characters and see them as role models for future behavior (Konijn et al. 2007).",
    "Despite these efforts, fictional goals like earning money for personal needs may make the decision to spread disinformation more relatable and justifiable to players (Musi et al. 2022)."
